uot%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.uber.com%2Fnewsroom%2Fwomeninthedriversseat%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DAnother%2520way%2520we%2527re%2520using%2Cor%2520off%2520whenever%2520they%2520choose.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Efeature%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20allows%20women%20drivers%20across%2030%20countries%20to%20express%20a%20preference%20for%20picking%20up%20women%20riders.%20But%20this%20feature%20is%20not%20yet%20available%20in%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDue%20to%20her%20safety%20concerns%2C%20Julie%20only%20drives%20during%20the%20daytime.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EAdditionally%2C%20after%20obtaining%20a%20firearms%20license%2C%20she%20said%20she%20now%20carries%20a%20handgun%20while%20she%20drives%20to%20help%20her%20feel%20safer.%20While%20Uber%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.uber.com%2Fus%2Fen%2Fsafety%2Fuber-community-guidelines%2Ffollow-law%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DRiders%2520and%2520their%2520guests%252C%2520as%2Cextent%2520permitted%2520by%2520applicable%2520law.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eprohibits%20drivers%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20carrying%20firearms%20while%20using%20the%20platform%2C%20some%20jurisdictions%20have%20laws%20that%20supersede%20this%20policy%2C%20a%20company%20spokesperson%20said.%20Julie%20said%20she%20has%20painstakingly%20reviewed%20the%20relevant%20policies%20and%20laws%20to%20ensure%20she%20is%20complying.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20taking%20the%20precautions%2C%20Julie%20said%20she%20still%20feels%20pressure%20to%20accept%20more%20rides%20than%20she's%20comfortable%20with%20to%20retain%20her%20Uber%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.uber.com%2Fus%2Fen%2Fdrive%2Fuber-pro%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Egold%20status%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20provides%20her%20access%20to%20certain%20perks%2C%20like%20lower%20gas%20expenses.%20To%20retain%20one's%20status%2C%20a%20driver%20needs%20to%20complete%20rides%20at%20a%20certain%20frequency.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20she%20also%20worries%20that%20a%20false%20customer%20complaint%20could%20get%20her%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftips-for-avoiding-deactivation-or-firing-uber-doordash-lyft-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ekicked%20off%20the%20Uber%20platform%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDrivers%20are%20left%20defenseless%2C%20worn%20out%2C%20and%20scared%20to%20even%20follow%20the%20law%20because%20we%20are%20constantly%20threatened%20with%20being%20deactivated%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EChecking%20a%20customer's%20profile%20and%20declining%20rides%20can%20reduce%20risks%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20she%20began%20driving%20roughly%20five%20years%20ago%2C%20Sara%2C%20a%20full-time%20Uber%20and%20Lyft%20driver%20in%20Chicago%2C%20said%20driving%20for%20both%20platforms%20has%20sometimes%20made%20her%20feel%20unsafe%20or%20uncomfortable.%20The%2064-year-old%2C%20who%20asked%20to%20use%20a%20pseudonym%20and%20spoke%20on%20condition%20of%20anonymity%20for%20fear%20of%20professional%20repercussions%2C%20said%20these%20incidents%20have%20typically%20involved%20intoxicated%20customers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20one%20occasion%2C%20she%20said%20a%20group%20of%20riders%20began%20making%20fun%20of%20her%20accent%2C%20an%20incident%20she%20said%20was%20humiliating%20and%20that%20she%20reported.%20In%20another%20instance%2C%20she%20said%20a%20customer%20asked%20her%20if%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eshe%20wanted%20to%20have%20sex%20%E2%80%94%20she%20said%20they%20backed%20off%20when%20she%20firmly%20declined.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20asked%20about%20Lyft's%20safety%20resources%2C%20a%20company%20spokesperson%20said%20that%20Lyft%20has%20an%20around-the-clock%20safety%20response%20team%20and%20works%20with%20leading%20national%20organizations%20to%20inform%20its%20safety%20policies.%20In%20September%2C%20Lyft%20launched%20a%20%26quot%3Bwomen%20connect%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.lyft.com%2Fwomen%2B%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Efeature%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%2055%20US%20cities%20that%20increases%20women%20drivers'%20odds%20of%20being%20matched%20with%20women%20riders.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSafety%20is%20fundamental%20to%20Lyft%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20spokesperson%20said.%20%26quot%3BSince%20day%20one%2C%20we%20have%20worked%20to%20design%20policies%20and%20features%20that%20protect%20both%20drivers%20and%20riders.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20response%20to%20her%20safety%20concerns%2C%20Sara%20said%20she%20doesn't%20drive%20at%20night%2C%20tries%20to%20stay%20close%20to%20home%2C%20and%20avoids%20speaking%20with%20customers%20about%20politics%20or%20other%20controversial%20topics.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20she%20said%20she%20always%20checks%20the%20customer's%20rating%20and%20pickup%20area.%20If%20she%20has%20a%20bad%20feeling%20about%20a%20ride%2C%20she%20cancels%20it.%20She%20recalled%20one%20past%20ride%20that%20came%20up%20on%20her%20Lyft%20app%3A%20a%20two-hour%20trip%20to%20Indiana%20for%20a%20passenger%20who%20had%20zero%20rides%2C%20no%20rating%2C%20and%20no%20picture.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20someone%20uses%20a%20nickname%20like%20'My%20King%2C'%20or%20an%20initial%20like%20'J'%20with%20no%20picture%2C%20it%20is%20a%20red%20flag%20for%20me%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20risk%20surpasses%20the%20compensation%20for%20the%20ride%2C%20and%20I%20will%20not%20take%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EAvoiding%20certain%20conversations%20can%20reduce%20the%20chances%20of%20conflict%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20years%2C%20Yvonne%2C%20a%20part-time%20Uber%20and%20Lyft%20driver%20in%20Tampa%2C%20Florida%2C%20said%20she's%20had%20very%20few%20trips%20that%20made%20her%20feel%20unsafe%20over%20her%20roughly%20seven%20years%20as%20a%20driver.%20But%20one%20particularly%20negative%20incident%20stands%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYvonne%2C%20who%20asked%20that%20her%20last%20name%20not%20be%20included%20for%20fear%20of%20professional%20repercussions%2C%20said%20a%20drunk%20customer%20propositioned%20her%20for%20sex%20and%20began%20hugging%20her%20until%20she%20was%20able%20to%20stop%20them.%20She%20said%20she%20probably%20should%20have%20reported%20this%20incident%20to%20the%20police%20but%20didn't.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYvonne%20said%20the%20best%20way%20to%20reduce%20safety%20concerns%20is%20to%20know%20when%20to%20talk%20%E2%80%94%20and%20when%20not%20to.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20you%20have%20one%20of%20those%20passengers%2C%20sometimes%20it%20is%20saying%20nothing%20at%20all%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BFor%20others%2C%20it%20is%20basically%20agreeing%20with%20them%2C%20even%20if%20you%20don't%20agree%2C%20or%20apologizing%20that%20they%20are%20having%20a%20bad%20day.%20It's%20more%20about%20being%20a%20people%20person%20and%20having%20the%20correct%20interpersonal%20skills%20to%20de-escalate%20a%20situation.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAre%20you%20a%20gig%20worker%20willing%20to%20share%20your%20story%20about%20pay%20and%20safety%3F%20If%20so%2C%20reach%20out%20to%20this%20reporter%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Ajzinkula%40insider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3Ejzinkula%40insider.com%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwomen-uber-lyft-driver-female-safety-tips-gig-economy-work-2023-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702465381000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F657782b658e7c0c29a2bdd4e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwomen-uber-lyft-driver-female-safety-tips-gig-economy-work-2023-12%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Three%20women%20Uber%20and%20Lyft%20drivers%20share%20advice%20for%20staying%20safe%20in%20the%20gig%20economy.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22jzin