emand.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENet%20legal%20immigration%20to%20Britain%20is%20currently%20running%20at%20750%2C000%20a%20year%20%E2%80%93%20that%E2%80%99s%20more%20than%201%25%20of%20the%20current%20population.%20The%20figure%20is%20consistently%20rising%20at%20the%20same%20time%20as%20ministers%20are%20pledging%20to%20bring%20it%20down.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20most%20contested%20aspect%20of%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20new%20immigration%20policy%20concerns%20the%20much%20smaller%20number%20of%20illegal%20immigrants%20%E2%80%93%20about%2030%2C000%20a%20year%20%E2%80%93%20who%20travel%20across%20the%20Channel%20on%20unseaworthy%20and%20overcrowded%20small%20boats.%20Sunak%20is%20persisting%20with%20his%20plans%20to%20deport%20asylum%20seekers%20to%20Rwanda%20in%20central%20Africa%2C%20even%20though%20that%E2%80%99s%20been%20rejected%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20government%20is%20introducing%20legislation%20which%20will%20sidestep%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20ruling%20by%20declaring%20Rwanda%20a%20safe%20destination%20for%20refugees%20%E2%80%93%20as%20if%20Parliament%20voting%20that%20the%20moon%20is%20made%20of%20cheese%20means%20that%20it%20really%20is.%20One%20wing%20of%20the%20Conservative%20Party%20views%20this%20as%20outrageously%20illiberal%3B%20another%20is%20complaining%20loudly%20that%20the%20government%20must%20go%20further%20and%20override%20the%20European%20Convention%20on%20Human%20Rights.%20The%20issue%20could%20precipitate%20a%20government%20defeat%20in%20Parliament%20which%20in%20turn%20may%20bring%20forward%20the%20next%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20for%20the%20time%20being%2C%20the%20advice%20has%20to%20be%3A%20if%20you%E2%80%99re%20thinking%20of%20marrying%20a%20Brit%2C%20beware!%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fauthor%2Ffrino%5C%22%3EAndrew%20Whitehead%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0is%20an%20honorary%20professor%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Nottingham%20in%20the%20UK%20and%20a%20former%