%20shops%2C%20and%20public%20spaces.%20These%20new%20projects%20won't%20have%20corporate%20logos%20on%20every%20building%2C%20and%20many%20of%20the%20units%20will%20be%20available%20to%20the%20general%20public%2C%20not%20just%20employees.%20But%20in%20the%20grand%20scheme%20of%20real%20estate%2C%20they're%20distinct%3A%20After%20years%20of%20running%20up%20against%20housing%20shortages%20in%20their%20backyards%2C%20companies%20like%20Google%2C%20Meta%2C%20and%20Disney%20%E2%80%94%20not%20exactly%20known%20for%20building%20new%20homes%20%E2%80%94%20are%20taking%20matters%20into%20their%20own%20hands.%20Their%20creations%20have%20boring%20names%20like%20Middlefield%20Park%20and%20Willow%20Village%2C%20but%20they%20might%20as%20well%20be%20called%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2018%2F03%2F21%2Ftechnology%2Ffacebook-zucktown-willow-village.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EZucktown%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20Google%20City%2C%20USA.%20And%20while%20the%20developments%20promise%20thousands%20of%20new%20homes%2C%20the%20plans%20are%20also%20a%20tacit%20acknowledgment%20of%20the%20bleak%20state%20of%20the%20American%20housing%20market%20and%20the%20roles%20these%20companies%20have%20played%20in%20driving%20up%20home%20prices%20near%20their%20sprawling%20HQs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20companies%20behind%20these%20projects%20argue%20that%20they%20can%20help%20solve%20the%20country's%20lack%20of%20affordable%20housing%2C%20but%20it's%20fair%20to%20approach%20the%20plans%20with%20a%20healthy%20degree%20of%20skepticism.%20America's%20single-employer%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcompany-town-history-facebook-2017-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecompany%20towns%3C%2Fa%3E''%20have%20a%20long%2C%20bloody%20history%20of%20exploitation%20and%20labor%20strife.%20While%20the%20current%20plans%20hardly%20represent%20a%20return%20to%20those%20dark%20days%20of%20the%2019th%20and%20early-20th%20centuries%2C%20they%20probably%20won't%20usher%20in%20a%20new%20era%20of%20futuristic%20techno-utopias%2C%20either.%20Judging%20by%20the%20plans%20that%20have%20been%20publicly%20unveiled%20so%20far%2C%20the%20Googles%20and%20Metas%20of%20the%20world%20aren't%20aiming%20nearly%20that%20high.%20Instead%2C%20their%20visions%20of%20city%20living%20spaces%20look%20a%20lot%20like%20what%20we're%20already%20used%20to%20seeing%20from%20modern%20real-estate%20developers%3A%20glassy%20office%20buildings%2C%20verdant%20parks%2C%20and%20walkable%20main%20streets%20with%20coffee%20shops%2C%20salad%20bars%2C%20and%20alluring%20apartment%20buildings.%20It's%20nice%2C%20but%20not%20exactly%20groundbreaking%20stuff.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERather%20than%20the%20floating%20cities%20or%20domed%20villages%20once%20dreamed%20up%20by%20science-fiction%20writers%20(%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffloating-city-plans-seasteading-institute-peter-thiel-blue-frontiers-2017-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eand%20Peter%20Thiel%3C%2Fa%3E)%2C%20these%20watered-down%20plans%20show%20that%20what%20these%20companies%20have%20been%20after%20all%20along%20is%20a%20way%20to%20one-up%20their%20competitors.%20They%20want%20to%20attract%20and%20retain%20top%20employees%2C%20and%20ideally%20get%20them%20back%20in%20the%20office%2C%20too.%20It%20doesn't%20hurt%20that%20right%20now%2C%20residential%20real%20estate%20looks%20like%20a%20pretty%20good%20bet.%20The%20noble%20aim%20of%20building%20more%20housing%2C%20including%20affordably%20priced%20units%2C%20is%20the%20cherry%20on%20top.%20But%20make%20no%20mistake%3A%20These%20companies%20will%20only%20pursue%20these%20plans%20as%20long%20as%20they%20fit%20their%20business%20goals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20modern%20company%20towns%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20years%20of%20planning%2C%20teasing%2C%20and%20slogging%20through%20local%20board%20meetings%2C%20the%20latest%20iterations%20of%20company%20towns%20are%20picking%20up%20steam.%20In%20June%2C%20Mountain%20View's%20city%20council%20approved%20the%20master%20plan%20for%20Google's%20North%20Bayshore%20project%2C%20a%20partnership%20between%20the%20tech%20giant%20and%20the%20Australian%20real-estate%20firm%20Lendlease.%20The%20new%20community%20will%20replace%20a%20suburban%20office%20park%20with%20a%20sprawling%20new%20neighborhood%20in%20the%20heart%20of%20Silicon%20Valley.%20The%20plans%20call%20for%20as%20many%20as%207%2C000%20new%20homes%20across%20%26quot%3Ba%20mix%20of%20income%20levels%2C%26quot%3B%20as%20well%20as%20parks%2C%20restaurants%2C%20shops%2C%20and%20more%20than%203%20million%20square%20feet%20of%20office%20space%20on%20153%20acres.%20Roughly%2015%25%20of%20those%20units%20will%20be%20priced%20below%20market%20rate%2C%20although%20the%20city%20hasn't%20settled%20upon%20the%20exact%20income%20thresholds%20that%20will%20determine%20who%20can%20apply%20for%20the%20units.%20Mountain%20View%20also%20greenlighted%20the%20master%20plan%20for%20Middlefield%20Park%2C%20another%20Google%20development%20that%20proposes%20to%20tear%20down%20existing%20office%20and%20industrial%20buildings%20and%20construct%20nearly%202%2C000%20new%20housing%20units%2C%20as%20well%20as%20more%20office%20and%20retail%20spaces.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20household%20names%20are%20getting%20in%20on%20the%20action.%20Last%20year%2C%20Menlo%20Park's%20city%20council%20voted%20unanimously%20in%20favor%20of%20the%20plans%20for%20Willow%20Village%2C%20Facebook's%2059-acre%20project%20that's%20also%20affectionately%2C%20or%20cynically%2C%20referred%20to%20as%20%26quot%3BZucktown.%26quot%3B%20It%20promises%20more%20than%201%2C700%20homes%2C%20as%20well%20as%20office%2C%20hotel%2C%20and%20retail%2C%20right%20next%20to%20Meta's%20headquarters%20at%201%20Hacker%20Way.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Fdisney-announces-groundbreaking-affordable-housing-florida-2023-04-20%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWalt%20Disney%20World%20also%20plans%20to%20break%20ground%3C%2Fa%3E%20next%20year%20on%201%2C400%20affordable%20housing%20units%20across%2080%20acres%20a%20few%20miles%20from%20its%20flagship%20theme%20park%20in%20Florida%2C%20the%20company%20said%20in%20the%20spring.%20Nearby%2C%20the%20competing%20resort%20company%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.orangeobserver.com%2Fnews%2F2023%2Fsep%2F22%2Funiversal-gives-update-on-affordable-housing-project%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUniversal%20is%20also%20building%201%2C000%20affordable%20apartments%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%2016%2C000%20square%20feet%20of%20retail%20space.%20While%20the%20companies%20will%20continue%20to%20own%20the%20land%20the%20homes%20will%20be%20built%20upon%2C%20in%20each%20of%20these%20cases%2C%20they're%20partnering%20with%20traditional%20real-estate%20firms%20to%20build%20and%20operate%20the%20buildings.%20In%20other%20words%2C%20you%20wouldn't%20end%20up%20cutting%20a%20rent%20check%20directly%20to%20Google.%20And%20anyone%20who%20meets%20the%20criteria%20can%20apply%20to%20rent%20the%20units%20%E2%80%94%20not%20just%20employees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225120%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20aerial%20view%20of%20renderings%20of%20apartment%20buildings%20that%20will%20be%20located%20on%2020%20acres%20at%20Catchlight%20Crossings%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6578b31a50edbc52a8636901%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222890%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAn%20aerial%20rendering%20of%20Catchlight%20Crossings%2C%20the%2020-acre%20affordable-housing%20development%20that%20will%20be%20built%20on%20land%20set%20aside%20by%20Universal%20Destinations%20%26amp%3B%20Experiences%20in%20Central%20Florida.%3Cp%3EWendover%20Housing%20Partners%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20companies%20are%20trying%20a%20different%20tack.%20Remember%20Amazon's%20HQ2%20hunt%3F%20The%20nationwide%20search%20had%20cities%20like%20Hartford%2C%20Connecticut%2C%20and%20Toledo%2C%20Ohio%2C%20tripping%20over%20themselves%20to%20offer%20the%20most%20generous%20economic%20incentives%20as%20the%20e-commerce%20titan%20searched%20for%20its%20second%20home%20and%20a%20place%20to%20put%20roughly%2025%2C000%20workers.%20The%20project%20ultimately%20landed%20in%20Arlington%2C%20Virginia%2C%20and%20the%20first%20phase%20of%20HQ2%20opened%20in%20May%2C%20with%20two%2022-story%20office%20buildings%20and%20a%20new%20public%20park.%20Amazon%20isn't%20building%20housing%20directly%20the%20way%20Google%20and%20Facebook%20are%2C%20but%20the%20%242%20billion%20Amazon%20Housing%20Equity%20Fund%20has%20committed%20to%20support%20other%20housing%20development%20in%20the%20DC%20area%2C%20Nashville%2C%20and%20Seattle%2C%20extending%20the%20company's%20direct%20influence%20beyond%20office%20space%20to%20housing%20markets%20that%20will%20almost%20surely%20feel%20the%20effects%20of%20its%20expansion%20for%20years%20to%20come.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20course%2C%20it%20wouldn't%20be%20a%20proper%20discussion%20of%20techno-utopias%20if%20Elon%20Musk's%20name%20didn't%20enter%20the%20chat.%20The%20embattled%20exec%20is%20reportedly%20laying%20the%20groundwork%20for%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-planning-build-snailbrook-town-for-texas-staff-report-2023-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enew%20town%20called%20Snailbrook%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20thousands%20of%20acres%20near%20Austin%2C%20where%20employees%20of%20his%20various%20companies%2C%20including%20the%20Boring%20Co.%2C%20Tesla%2C%20and%20SpaceX%2C%20could%20one%20day%20live%20at%20below-market%20prices.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20no%20surprise%20that%20the%20largest%20of%20the%20new%20developments%20are%20the%20brainchildren%20of%20Silicon%20Valley%20giants.%20The%20modern%20tech%20industry%20was%20built%20on%20a%20California-tinted%20brand%20of%20utopianism%20and%20the%20belief%20that%20%26quot%3Bconnecting%20people%26quot%3B%20is%20the%20answer%20to%20many%20of%20the%20world's%20problems%2C%20Grant%20Bollmer%2C%20a%20senior%20lecturer%20in%20digital%20media%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Queensland%20in%20Australia%2C%20told%20me.%20After%20all%20the%20digital%20ad%20dollars%20have%20been%20hoovered%20up%20and%20all%20the%20attention%20squeezed%20out%20of%20our%20screen-addled%20eyeballs%2C%20the%20next%20logical%20step%20is%20building%20a%20new%20city%20where%20the%20founding%20principles%20of%20the%20tech%20world%20can%20be%20put%20into%20practice.%20Just%20look%20at%20the%20pie-in-the-sky%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcalifornia-forever-silicon-valley-billionaire-city-plans-are-terrible-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eplans%20for%20California%20Forever%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20proposal%20from%20Silicon%20Valley%20elites%20to%20turn%2055%2C000%20acres%20of%20rural%20land%20into%20the%20city%20of%20the%20future.%20Billionaires%20with%20time%20on%20their%20hands%2C%20it%20seems%2C%20simply%20can't%20help%20themselves.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFaith%20in%20democracy%20is%20weak%2C%20and%20so%20you%20have%20this%20view%20of%2C%20'We%20can%20create%20an%20ideal%20city%20and%20ideal%20world%2C'%26quot%3B%20Bollmer%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3B'We%20can%20structure%20it%20according%20to%20the%20principles%20that%20are%20built%20into%20these%20technologies%20that%20we've%20created%20and%20the%20values%20that%20we've%20created.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20companies%20are%20also%20ruthlessly%20pragmatic%2C%20profit-making%20machines%20beholden%20to%20shareholders%20who%20closely%20watch%20their%20every%20move.%20High-minded%20ideals%20aside%2C%20the%20modern%20company%20towns%20also%20make%20for%20sound%20business%20propositions%2C%20Margaret%20Crawford%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20architecture%20and%20chair%20of%20the%20urban%20design%20program%20at%20the%20University%20of%20California%2C%20Berkeley%2C%20told%20me.%20These%20firms%20are%20interested%20in%20two%20things%3A%20retaining%20skilled%20labor%20and%20drumming%20up%20positive%20publicity%20that%20makes%20them%20look%20civic-minded.%20Building%20housing%20near%20their%20HQs%20checks%20off%20both%20those%20boxes%3A%20Commuting%20is%20the%20top%20reason%20employees%20don't%20want%20to%20go%20back%20to%20the%20office%20full%20time%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gallup.com%2Fworkplace%2F474482%2Fwhy-commute.aspx%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGallup%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20while%20the%20lack%20of%20affordable%20housing%20in%20cities%20is%20forcing%20more%20people%20to%20move%20further%20from%20where%20offices%20are%20often%20located%2C%20research%20from%20Fannie%20Mae%20found.%20In%20a%20recent%20piece%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhbr.org%2F2023%2F03%2Fwhat-employers-can-do-to-address-high-housing-costs%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EHarvard%20Business%20Review%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20economist%20Edward%20Glaeser%20and%20the%20consultant%20Atta%20Tarki%20argued%20that%20companies%20should%20think%20of%20housing%20assistance%20as%20just%20one%20part%20of%20a%20broader%20benefits%20package%2C%20next%20to%20on-site%20chefs%20or%20an%20office%20gym%2C%20that%20encourages%20employees%20to%20stick%20around%20and%20be%20more%20productive.%20Even%20if%20these%20projects%20aren't%20explicitly%20for%20employees%2C%20it's%20conceivable%20that%20they'll%20be%20favored%20by%20workers%20who%20are%20eager%20to%20skip%20all%20that%20traffic%20on%20the%20way%20to%20their%20desks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAffordable%20housing%20near%20offices%20makes%20for%20good%20press%20and%20also%20makes%20good%20business%20sense.%20But%20the%20second%20new%20housing%20doesn't%20fit%20a%20business'%20goals%20%E2%80%94%20if%20a%20company%20is%20slashing%20jobs%20or%20abandoning%20office%20space%20%E2%80%94%20they'll%20probably%20pump%20the%20brakes%20on%20grand%20plans%20for%20a%20new%20neighborhood%20as%20well.%20Crafting%20new%20cities%20is%20complicated%2C%20time-intensive%20work.%20And%20if%20history%20has%20taught%20us%20anything%2C%20it's%20that%20they%20are%20often%20doomed%20to%20fail.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20worrying%20history%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20towns%20of%20the%2019th%20and%2020th%20centuries%20also%20bore%20some%20of%20that%20utopian%20flavor%2C%20at%20least%20in%20theory.%20In%20many%20cases%2C%20company%20towns%20were%20a%20practical%20response%20to%20the%20need%20for%20housing%20near%20factories%20or%20lumber%20mills%2C%20which%20were%20typically%20located%20in%20barren%20locations%20without%20the%20kinds%20of%20amenities%20that%20would%20keep%20workers%20happy%2C%20like%20churches%20or%20libraries.%20The%20Hershey%20Company%20town%20in%20Pennsylvania%2C%20founded%20around%201909%2C%20prioritized%20these%20kinds%20of%20community%20assets%20from%20the%20start%2C%20while%20also%20offering%20affordable%20homes%20that%20workers%20could%20rent%20or%20own.%20At%20one%20point%2C%203%25%20of%20the%20US%20population%20lived%20in%20company%20towns%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.economist.com%2Fbooks-and-arts%2F2010%2F10%2F14%2Fmonuments-to-power%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Economist%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20idea%20of%20a%20place%20dominated%20by%20a%20single%20corporation%20%E2%80%94%20where%20your%20boss%20not%20only%20owns%20your%20home%20but%20also%20runs%20your%20church%20and%20your%20kids'%20schools%20and%20sells%20you%20everything%20you%20need%20at%20the%20company%20store%20%E2%80%94%20was%20always%20a%20fraught%20proposition.%20In%20many%20company%20towns%2C%20the%20corporations%20used%20the%20setup%20to%20maintain%20their%20social%20control%2C%20threatening%20disgruntled%20workers%20with%20eviction%20from%20company%20housing%20if%20they%20went%20on%20strike.%20When%20your%20company%20is%20your%20entire%20world%2C%20the%20stakes%20are%20infinitely%20higher.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOne%20of%20the%20things%20that%20happens%20sort%20of%20quickly%20is%20people%20begin%20to%20view%20the%20company%20as%20the%20golden%20goose%2C%26quot%3B%20Hardy%20Green%2C%20the%20author%20of%20%26quot%3BThe%20Company%20Town%3A%20The%20Industrial%20Edens%20and%20Satanic%20Mills%20that%20Shaped%20the%20American%20Economy%2C%26quot%3B%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BThey%20don't%20want%20to%20do%20anything%20that%20offends%20the%20company.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECompany%20towns%20gradually%20disintegrated%20as%20workers'%20wages%20rose%20and%20they%20gained%20access%20to%20cars%2C%20which%20enabled%20them%20to%20live%20farther%20from%20the%20factories%20and%20achieve%20more%20autonomy.%20Today%2C%20the%20experiment%20is%20mostly%20remembered%20as%20a%20failure%2C%20characterized%20by%20poor%20working%20conditions%20and%20frequent%20clashes%20with%20unions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThis%20time%20is%20different%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EGiven%20the%20history%20of%20company-built%20housing%2C%20it's%20fair%20to%20wonder%20which%20way%20the%20new%20iterations%20will%20lean%3A%20toward%20the%20idealized%20version%20of%20cheaper%20housing%20and%20prized%20amenities%2C%20or%20a%20more%20dystopian%20outcome%20in%20which%20we%20become%20more%20reliant%20on%20companies%20that%20have%20already%20infiltrated%20every%20aspect%20of%20our%20lives.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20graveyard%20of%20abandoned%20projects%20may%20offer%20some%20clues%20as%20to%20what%20comes%20next.%20In%20May%202020%2C%20Sidewalk%20Labs%2C%20an%20offshoot%20of%20Google's%20parent%20company%2C%20Alphabet%2C%20walked%20away%20from%20plans%20to%20build%20a%20new%2C%20tech-heavy%20neighborhood%20on%2012%20acres%20along%20Toronto's%20waterfront.%20The%20company%20officially%20said%20its%20partnership%20with%20the%20city%20folded%20because%20of%20the%20pandemic%2C%20but%20it%20turned%20out%20that%20the%20company%20had%20been%20quietly%20making%20plans%20to%20acquire%20800%20acres%20of%20adjacent%20land%20for%20an%20entire%20Google%20campus%20and%20a%20testing%20ground%20for%20some%20of%20its%20wilder%20technologies.%20When%20it%20unveiled%20those%20plans%2C%20both%20the%20public%20and%20local%20elected%20officials%20turned%20against%20the%20idea%2C%20stymieing%20and%20eventually%20killing%20the%20whole%20project.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGoogle's%20representatives%20had%20pitched%20the%20initial%20neighborhood%20as%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsidewalk-labs-ceo-dan-doctoroff-master-plan-2019-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20most%20innovative%20district%20in%20the%20entire%20world%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20so%20maybe%20it%20shouldn't%20have%20been%20a%20surprise%20that%20its%20ambitions%20extended%20far%20beyond%20a%20mere%2012%20acres.%20But%20the%20missteps%2C%20and%20the%20eventual%20death%20of%20the%20project%2C%20reflected%20a%20fundamental%20misunderstanding%20of%20how%20developers%20work%20with%20city%20governments%2C%20Josh%20O'Kane%2C%20a%20reporter%20who%20closely%20chronicled%20the%20plans%20for%20Toronto's%20Globe%20and%20Mail%20newspaper%20and%20later%20wrote%20a%20book%20on%20the%20whole%20saga%2C%20told%20me.%20All%20the%20money%20in%20the%20world%20couldn't%20turn%20public%20opinion%2C%20and%20the%20local%20quasi-governmental%20partners%20refused%20to%20be%20steamrolled.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGoogle's%20plans%20in%20Mountain%20View%2C%20by%20comparison%2C%20are%20much%20tamer.%20All%20that%20talk%20about%20a%20city%20of%20the%20future%20has%20been%20replaced%20with%20language%20touting%20affordable%20housing%20and%20more%20traditional%20spaces%20for%20local%20businesses%20and%20public%20parks.%20The%20project%20is%20still%20huge%2C%20to%20be%20sure%2C%20but%20Google%20had%20once%20talked%20about%20playing%20%26quot%3Ba%20much%20bigger%20role%20in%20public%20life%26quot%3B%20than%20what's%20outlined%20in%20the%20current%20plans%2C%20O'Kane%20told%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMaybe%20Google%2C%20and%20other%20big%20companies%2C%20did%20learn%20a%20lesson%20from%20that%20debacle%20in%20Toronto.%20It%20certainly%20