a.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Fnetizens-think-that-the-axe-sequence-in-ranbir-kapoor-starrer-animal-is-inspired-from-this-korean-and-malayalam-movie-watch-videos%2Farticleshow%2F105955624.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F105955624.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EThese%20clips%20from%20a%20Korean%20movie%20and%20a%20Malayalam%20movie%20have%20gone%20viral%20on%20the%20internet%20and%20people%20think%20the%20action%20sequences%20of%20'Animal'%20are%20copied%20from%20them...%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Fnetizens-think-that-the-axe-sequence-in-ranbir-kapoor-starrer-animal-is-inspired-from-this-korean-and-malayalam-movie-watch-videos%2Farticleshow%2F105955624.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Stubble-Burning%20Incidents%20Down%20by%2054.2%25%20in%20the%20Latest%20Paddy%20Harvesting%20Season%3A%20Centre%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F12%2F14145605%2F6314806215_7aa3972351_b.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3EStubble-burning%20incidents%20in%20states%20with%20major%20paddy%20cultivation%20have%20reduced%20by%2054.2%25%20during%20the%20recent%2045-day%20paddy%20harvesting%20season%20in%20comparison%20to%20the%20same%20period%20last%20year%2C%20the%20Union%20government%20told%20parliament.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPaddy%20stubble%20burning%20is%20the%20practice%20of%20burning%20leftover%20plant%20debris%20after%20harvesting%20rice%20to%20prepare%20fields%20for%20wheat%20crops.%20The%20Union%20government%20data%20estimates%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fsci-tech%2Fenergy-and-environment%2Fdelhi-pollution-woes-majorly-due-to-stubble-burning-centre%2Farticle67518519.ece%23%3A~%3Atext%3DCentral%2520government%2520sources%2520said%252038%2Cwas%2520contributed%2520by%2520stubble%2520burning.%5C%22%3E38%25%20of%20the%20air%20pollution%20level%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20contributed%20by%20stubble%20burning.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20data%20presented%20by%20Union%20agriculture%20and%20farmers%E2%80%99%20welfare%20minister%2C%20Arjun%20Munda%2C%20to%20the%20parliament%20on%20Tuesday%2C%20December%2012%2C%20the%20number%20of%20incidents%20reduced%20from%2013%2C964%20(in%202022)%20to%206%2C391%20(in%202023)%20during%20the%20September%2015%20to%20October%2029%20period%20across%20Punjab%2C%20Haryana%2C%20NCR-Uttar%20Pradesh%2C%20NCR-Rajasthan%2C%20and%20Delhi.%20In%202021%2C%20these%20regions%20together%20accounted%20for%2011%2C461%20stubble-burning%20incidents%20in%20the%20same%20period.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPunjab%20and%20Haryana%20had%20registered%2012%2C112%20and%201%2C813%20incidents%2C%20respectively%2C%20in%202022.%20The%20corresponding%20figures%20for%20this%20year%20came%20down%20to%205%2C254%20and%201%2C094%20in%20the%20September%2015%20to%20October%2029%20period.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20agriculture%20minister%20told%20the%20House%20that%20a%20satellite%20remote%20sensing%20system%20is%20in%20place%20to%20track%20active%20fires.%20The%20system%20was%20developed%20by%20the%20Consortium%20for%20Research%20on%20Agroecosystem%20Monitoring%20and%20Modelling%20from%20Space%20Laboratory%2C%20Division%20of%20Agricultural%20Physics%2C%20ICAR-Indian%20Agricultural%20Research%20Institute%2C%20New%20Delhi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20June%2010%2C%202021%2C%20the%20Commission%20for%20Air%20Quality%20Management%2C%20through%20statutory%20directions%2C%20came%20out%20with%20a%20framework%20for%20control%2Felimination%20of%20crop%20residue%20burning%2C%20mandating%20governments%20of%20Punjab%2C%20Haryana%2C%20and%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20to%20develop%20state-specific%20actionable%20plans.%20The%20plans%2C%20the%20minister%20said%2C%20include%20proper%20implementation%20of%20in-situ%20and%20ex-situ%20management%20of%20paddy%20straw%2C%20effective%20monitoring%2Fenforcement%2C%20and%20the%20prohibition%20of%20stubble%20burning.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20the%20overall%20air%20quality%20in%20Delhi%20stood%20in%20the%20%E2%80%98very%20poor%E2%80%99%20category%20with%20the%20Air%20Quality%20Index%20(AQI)%20standing%20at%20326%2C%20as%20per%20Central%20Pollution%20Control%20Board%20(CPCB)%20data%20registered%20at%207%20am%20on%20Tuesday%2C%20December%2012%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livemint.com%2Fnews%2Fdelhi-no-longer-indias-most-polluted-city-bihar-uttar-pradesh-sees-worst-aqi-check-full-list-here-11702342673449.html%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20%3Cem%3ELiveMint%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20An%20AQI%20between%20zero%20and%2050%20is%20considered%20%E2%80%98good%E2%80%99%2C%2051%20and%20100%20%E2%80%98satisfactory%E2%80%99%2C%20101%20and%20200%20%E2%80%98moderate%E2%80%99%2C%20201%20and%20300%20%E2%80%98poor%E2%80%99%2C%20301%20and%20400%20%E2%80%98very%20poor%E2%80%99%2C%20401%20and%20450%20%E2%80%98severe%E2%80%99%20and%20above%20450%20%E2%80%98severe-plus%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702452601000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F12%2F14145605%2F6314806215_7aa3972351_b.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fstubble-burning-incidents-down-by-54-2-in-the-latest-paddy-harvesting-season-centre%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20number%20of%20incidents%20reduced%20from%2013%2C964%20(in%202022)%20to%206%2C391%20(in%202023)%20during%20the%20September%2015%20to%20October%2029%20period%20across%20Punjab%2C%20Haryana%2C%20NCR-Uttar%20Pradesh%2C%20NCR-Rajasthan%2C%20and%20Delhi.%20Data%20suggests%20that%2038%25%20of%20the%20air%20pollution%20level%20is%20contributed%20by%20stubble%20burning.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22