e%20people%20familiar%20with%20the%20operation.%20They%20spoke%20on%20the%20condition%20of%20anonymity%20to%20describe%20sensitive%20intelligence%20activities.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERAW%20has%20been%20in%20the%20news%20recently%20in%20connection%20with%20alleged%20assassination%20plots%20in%20Canada%20and%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Cem%3EWashington%20Post%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20after%20reviewing%20%E2%80%9C100%2C000%20reposts%20of%20Disinfo%20Lab%20content%20on%20X%E2%80%9D%20writes%20that%20the%20Disinfo%20Lab%20%E2%80%9Chas%20published%20lengthy%20dossiers%20and%20social%20media%20posts%20claiming%20to%20reveal%20the%20personal%20relationships%20and%20funding%20sources%20behind%20U.S.-based%20critics%20of%20Indian%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Disinfo%20Lab%20%E2%80%9Ccombined%20fact-based%20research%20with%20unsubstantiated%20claims%20to%20paint%20U.S.%20government%20figures%2C%20researchers%2C%20humanitarian%20groups%20and%20Indian%20American%20rights%20activists%20as%20part%20of%20a%20conspiracy%2C%20purportedly%20led%20by%20global%20Islamic%20groups%20and%20billionaire%20George%20Soros%2C%20to%20undermine%20India.%E2%80%9D%20The%20news%20report%20records%20how%20these%20allegations%20went%20viral%20on%20Indian%20social%20media%20%E2%80%9Cafter%20they%20were%20amplified%20by%20pro-Modi%20influencers%2C%20who%20at%20times%20used%20the%20group%E2%80%99s%20findings%20to%20validate%20their%20own%20positions.%20Its%20reports%20have%20been%20cited%20by%20Indian%20officials%20on%20television%20and%20presented%20on%20Capitol%20Hill.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Disinfo%20Lab%20%E2%80%9Cdoes%20not%20disclose%20its%20affiliation%2C%20describing%20itself%20on%20its%20website%20as%20a%20%E2%80%98separate%20legal%20entity%E2%80%99%20that%20seeks%20to%20offer%20%E2%80%98completely%20unbiased%20research.%E2%80%99%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20past%20five%20years%2C%20the%20newspaper%20records%20how%20%E2%80%9Csocial%20media%20researchers%20have%20uncovered%20large%20Indian%20online%20networks%20that%20promote%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20foreign%20policy%20positions%20to%20domestic%20and%20foreign%20audiences.%E2%80%9D%20Coordinated%20social%20media%20accounts%20have%20been%20found%20to%20play%20a%20role%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20in%20spreading%20identical%20posts%20in%20support%20of%20Russia%2C%20an%20important%20supplier%20of%20weapons%20and%20energy%20to%20India%2C%20and%20of%20Israel%2C%20an%20increasingly%20close%20partner.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESatpathy%20is%20said%20to%20have%20met%20%E2%80%9CWestern%20journalists%20and%20commentators%20under%20fake%20identities%20%E2%80%94%20including%20his%20preferred%20alias%2C%20Shakti%2C%20meaning%20%E2%80%9Cpower%E2%80%9D%20in%20Hindi%20%E2%80%94%20and%20sought%20favorable%20coverage%20of%20India%20or%20critical%20coverage%20of%20its%20adversaries%2C%20Pakistan%20and%20China%2C%20according%20to%20five%20additional%20people%20who%20have%20had%20contact%20with%20Satpathy.%E2%80%9D%20The%20Disinfo%20Lab%20though%2C%20denies%20any%20connection%20with%20government%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%20are%20in%20no%20form%20associated%20with%20any%20govt%20agency%2C%20nor%20with%20any%20of%20its%20personnel.%20Nor%20are%20we%20associated%20with%20any%20other%20organization%20%E2%80%94%20Indian%20or%20International%E2%80%9D%2C%20they%20told%20the%20Post.%20It%20said%20it%20was%20created%20by%20individuals%20%E2%80%9Cwho%20had%20met%20in%20an%20anti-corruption%20political%20movement%E2%80%9D%20and%20were%20concerned%20about%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20massive%20disinformation%20targeted%20at%20India%20to%20sow%20divisions%20in%20society.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FDisinfoLab%2Fstatus%2F1734075357144498602%5C%22%3EOn%20X%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20Disinfo%20Lab%20called%20the%20%3Cem%3EWashington%20Post%3C%2Fem%3E%20article%20a%20%E2%80%9Cbarely%20disguised%20revenge%20piece%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20Indian%20right%20wing%20is%20a%20new%20player%20that%20has%20arrived%20on%20the%20world%20stage%20and%20wants%20to%20shape%20global%20discussion%2C%E2%80%9D%20Joyojeet%20Pal%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20information%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Michigan%20who%20studies%20disinformation%20in%20India%20is%20quoted%20by%20%3Cem%3EWashington%20Post%3C%2Fem%3E%20as%20saying.%20%E2%80%9CSo%20far%2C%20much%20of%20it%20is%20done%20in%20the%20same%20way%20it%E2%80%99s%20done%20within%20India%20%E2%80%94%20through%20crude%2C%20blunt%20force.%20But%20it%E2%80%99s%20getting%20smarter.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Disinfo%20Lab%20has%20emerged%20as%20%E2%80%9Cone%20of%20the%20more%20sophisticated%20players%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20avers%20as%20in%20it%20%E2%80%9C28%20reports%20it%20has%20published%20so%20far%2C%20the%20organization%20has%20often%20painted%20a%20picture%20of%20an%20India%20under%20attack%20by%20a%20sprawling%20%E2%80%9Cnexus%E2%80%9D%20of%20conspirators%20funded%20by%20Pakistani%20intelligence%2C%20the%20Muslim%20Brotherhood%20and%20Soros.%E2%80%9D%20The%20%3Cem%3EWashington%20Post%3C%2Fem%3E%20reports%20of%20the%20influential%20retweeters%2C%20end%20up%20giving%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20Disinfo%20Lab%20a%20stamp%20of%20authority%20and%2C%20some%20of%20its%20targets%20say%2C%20boost%20its%20ability%20to%20intimidate%20individuals%20overseas%E2%80%9D%2C%20when%20in%20effect%20it%20is%20allegedly%20connected%20with%20%E2%80%9CIndia%E2%80%99s%20intelligence%20operation.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESumit%20Ganguly%2C%20an%20expert%20on%20Indian%20diplomacy%20and%20national%20security%20at%20Indiana%20University%20at%20Bloomington%20in%20the%20US%20told%20the%20newspaper%20that%20undermining%20foreign%20governments%20and%20their%20officials%20is%20%E2%80%9Croutine%E2%80%9D%20work%20for%20all%20intelligence%20agencies.%20But%2C%20he%20is%20quoted%20as%20saying%2C%20if%20Indian%20intelligence%20is%20%E2%80%9Cbesmirching%20American%20critics%20and%20civil%20society%20organizations%2C%20it%20would%20be%20crossing%20a%20line%20reminiscent%20of%20KGB%20tactics%20during%20the%20Cold%20War%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%20%E2%80%9CIt%20would%20be%20part%20and%20parcel%20of%20the%20Modi%20government%E2%80%99s%20attitude%20toward%20dissent%2C%20whether%20at%20home%20or%20abroad.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESatpathy%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20comments.%20India%E2%80%99s%20national%20security%20adviser%2C%20Ajit%20Doval%2C%20too%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20the%20newspaper.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702445818000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F13105929%2FScreenshot-2023-12-13-at-10.12.02%25E2%2580%25AFAM.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsecurity%2Fdisinfo-lab-which-claims-conspiracies-against-modi-govt-run-by-a-raw-officer-washington-post%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Disinfo%20Lab%20has%20published%20reports%20alleging%20misinformation%20conspiracies%20by%20Islamists%20and%20Soros.%20It%20denies%20ties%20to%20government%2C%20says%20run%20by%20those%20%E2%80%9Cwho%20had%20met%20in%20an%20anti-corruption%20political%20movement%E2%80%9D%20and%20were%20concerned%20about%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20massive%20disinformation%20targeted%20at%20India%20to%20sow%20divisions%E2%80%9D.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsecurity%2Fdisinfo-lab-which-claims-conspiracies-against-modi-govt-run-by-a-raw-officer-washington-post%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Bihar%20Caste%20Survey%3A%20The%20Who%E2%80%99s%20Who%20in%20the%20Data%20%7C%20Kumhar%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F13105029%2F22478674358_52cc3c7bdf_c.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EBeyond%20politics%2C%20the%20Bihar%20caste%20survey%20is%20a%20revolutionary%20document.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EA%20public%20document%2C%20the%20first%20ever%20after%201931%2C%20allowing%20for%20people%20to%20stand%20up%20and%20be%20counted.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EWe%20go%20down%20to%20the%20wire%2C%20on%20what%20each%20of%20the%20numbers%20unveiled%20mean.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EWho%20are%20the%20people%20referred%20to%20by%20percentages%20in%20the%20survey%3F%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3EToday%20we%20look%20at%20Kumhar%20(1%2C834%2C418%20people)%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A7%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOne%20cannot%20pinpoint%20with%20certainty%20as%20to%20which%20community%20was%20the%20first%20to%20inhabit%20this%20earth.%20However%2C%20it%20does%20appear%20that%20potters%2C%20or%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EKumhars%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20%E2%80%93%20the%20caste%20group%20which%20we%20are%20going%20to%20discuss%20today%20%E2%80%93%20must%20be%20among%20the%20earliest%20inhabitants%20who%20understood%20the%20power%20of%20speed.%20They%20also%20must%20have%20been%20the%20first%20to%20recognise%20the%20significance%20of%20clay.%20As%20a%20result%20of%20this%20understanding%2C%20they%20must%20have%20invented%20the%20wheel%20and%20gone%20on%20to%20create%20various%20types%20of%20utensils.%20They%20were%20also%20the%20ones%20to%20make%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20earthen%20lamps%2C%20to%20light%20the%20way%20in%20darkness.%20This%20is%20perhaps%20why%20they%20are%20also%20called%20%E2%80%9CKumhar%20Pandit%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%93%20because%20the%20literal%20meaning%20of%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Epanditya%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20is%20%E2%80%98creation%E2%80%99%20and%20it%20is%20a%20word%20which%20is%20related%20to%20knowledge.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20399px)%2085vw%2C%20399px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F30093107%2FIMG_2742.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22399%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F30093107%2FIMG_2742.jpg%20838w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F30093107%2FIMG_2742-210x300.jpg%20210w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F30093107%2FIMG_2742-715x1024.jpg%20715w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-682410%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22571%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EIllustration%3A%20Pariplab%20Chakraborty%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIf%20one%20looks%20at%20representations%20of%20the%20Stone%20Ages%2C%20one%20will%20find%20potters%20with%20their%20wheel%20and%20plenty%20of%20clay.%20They%20are%20a%20most%20important%20link%20to%20the%20development%20of%20human%20civilisation.%20But%20it%20is%20not%20easy%20to%20create%20something.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPotters%20have%20existed%20in%20different%20forms%20not%20only%20in%20Bihar%20or%20India%2C%20but%20in%20all%20the%20civilisations%20across%20the%20world.%20The%20utensils%20unearthed%20from%20Egyptian%20sites%20are%20an%20evidence%20of%20it.%20People%20made%20utensils%20and%20terracotta%20sculptures%20during%20the%20Harappan%20period%20too.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20it%20is%20also%20true%20that%20despite%20being%20skilled%20craftsmen%2C%20potter%20have%20been%20a%20neglected.%20There%20are%20other%20artisan%20groups%2C%20too%2C%20which%20are%20not%20mentioned%20in%20detail%20in%20history%20books.%20The%20connection%20of%20kumhars%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20to%20the%20Ajivaka%20religion%2C%20before%20Buddhism%2C%20is%20established%20through%20Ajivaka%20Sanjay%20Keshakambali%2C%20who%20hailed%20from%20a%20potter%20family.%20But%20there%20are%20no%20more%20details%20available%20about%20it%20in%20Buddhist%20texts.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20Bihar%2C%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20and%20West%20Bengal%20potters%20are%20counted%20as%20%3Cem%3Ep%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3Eawaniya%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cspan%3E%20just%20like%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Enai%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Elohar%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Ebadhai%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20and%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Ekahar%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20The%20job%20of%20p%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eawaniya%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0people%20is%20to%20serve.%20That%E2%80%99s%20what%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ekumhars%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ealso%20do.%20When%20people%20get%20married%2C%20potters%20make%20clay%20elephants%2C%20horses%2C%20birds%2C%20and%20other%20such%20figures%20for%20them.%20They%20also%20make%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3Ekalash%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20a%20pot%20in%20which%20water%20is%20kept%20as%20part%20of%20a%20Hindu%20wedding%20ritual.%20Earlier%2C%20they%20used%20to%20get%20money%20and%20clothes%20in%20return.%20But%20times%20have%20changed%20now%20and%20there%20is%20a%20price%20on%20every%20item%20they%20manufacture.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EKumhars%20comprise%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20both%20Hindus%20and%20Muslims.%20But%2C%20in%20Hinduism%2C%20Brahminism%20has%20snatched%20their%20identity%20from%20them%20and%20now%20they%20are%20referred%20to%20as%20%E2%80%98Prajapati%E2%80%99.%20Vedic%20stories%20have%20been%20concocted%20so%20that%20this%20community%20with%20tribal%20roots%20can%20be%20Hinduised.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20people%20of%20Kumhar%20community%20follow%20tribal%20traditions.%20In%20the%20Hindu%20religious%20text%20%3Cem%3EYajurved%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20they%20have%20been%20highlighted%20as%20%E2%80%98Prajapati%E2%80%99.%20Prajapati%20was%20the%20son%20of%20Brahma%2C%20the%20way%20Saraswati%20was%20his%20daughter.%20Brahmins%20consider%20both%20Prajapati%20and%20Saraswati%20wise.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20this%20does%20not%20establish%20that%20Kumhars%20are%20the%20descendants%20of%20Prajapati.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20fact%20is%20that%20in%20the%20original%20term%20%E2%80%98%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ekumhar%E2%80%99%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20where%20%E2%80%98%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ekum%E2%80%99%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20stands%20for%20pond%20or%20water%20body.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20term%20must%20have%20resulted%20from%20the%20fact%20that%20potters%20require%20both%20soil%20and%20water%20for%20their%20work.%20But%20not%20every%20type%20of%20soil%20sticks%20to%20the%20wheel%2C%20especially%20the%20sand-mixed%20soil%20found%20on%20the%20banks%20of%20rivers.%20They%20require%20loamy%20soil%20or%20black%20soil%2C%20which%20is%20sticky%20and%20moldable.%20It%20can%20be%20assumed%20that%20they%20dug%20the%20earth%20and%20saw%20that%20the%20pit%20thus%20formed%20when%20filled%20with%20water%20during%20rainy%20season%20gives%20a%20suitable%20clayey%20soil.%20Even%20today%2C%20potters%20often%20live%20on%20the%20banks%20of%20ponds%20and%20reservoirs%20which%20have%20stagnant%20water.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHowever%2C%20their%20name%20was%20changed%20according%20to%20the%20things%20they%20made.%20For%20instance%2C%20a%20pitcher%20is%20called%20%3Cem%3Ek%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3Eumbh%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cspan%3E%20in%20Sanskrit%20and%20so%2C%20they%20were%20called%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Ekumbhkar%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Einstead%20of%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ekumhar%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20So%2C%20considering%20that%20the%20people%20of%20this%20caste%20group%20make%20lots%20of%20other%20things%20like%20pots%2C%20lamps%2C%20utensils%20and%20idols%2C%20and%20not%20just%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ekumbhs%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Ewhy%20were%20they%20referred%20to%20as%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ekumbhkars%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%3F%20One%20does%20not%20know.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20Dravidian%20traditions%2C%20too%2C%20they%20are%20called%20K%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eumhar%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20In%20today%E2%80%99s%20Pakistan%E2%80%99s%20Punjab%20province%2C%20they%20are%20also%20called%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Ekulal%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20Their%20community%20is%20spread%20across%20every%20state%20of%20India.%20They%20are%20not%20treated%20as%20untouchable%20in%20most%20of%20the%20provinces%2C%20and%20they%20do%20not%20enjoy%20social%20prestige.%20In%20Hindi-speaking%20states%2C%20especially%20Bihar%20and%20Uttar%20Pradesh%2C%20they%20are%20counted%20among%20the%20Pawaniyas%20and%20are%20specially%20given%20place%20to%20settle%20so%20that%20they%20can%20serve%20the%20%E2%80%98upper%E2%80%99%20castes.%20Moreover%2C%20had%20they%20been%20considered%20untouchable%2C%20who%20would%20carve%20the%20idols%20of%20gods%3F%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20this%20does%20not%20mean%20that%20they%20have%20equal%20rights%20to%20resources%20to%20which%20social%20prestige%20is%20directly%20related.%20They%20are%20not%20settled%20in%20villages%20like%20other%20Other%20Backward%20Class%20or%20Dalit%20castes.%20Sometimes%2C%20villages%20have%20only%20a%20couple%20of%20K%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eumhar%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Efamilies%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3EThere%20is%20not%20a%20single%20village%20in%20Bihar%20and%20UP%20which%20belongs%20solely%20to%20the%20people%20of%20the%20K%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eumhar%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20caste.%20At%20some%20places%20one%20can%20see%20a%20Kumhar%20Toli%20or%20Kumhar%20Tola%20but%20the%20size%20of%20the%20colony%20is%20very%20small.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20present%20times%2C%20social%20prestige%20is%20also%20related%20to%20numbers.%20In%20Bihar%2C%20a%20state%20with%20a%20population%20of%2013%20crores%2C%20the%20number%20of%20the%20people%20of%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EKumhar%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20caste%20is%20only%201%2C834%2C418%2C%20according%20to%20the%20caste-based%20census%20report%20of%202022%20released%20by%20the%20Bihar%20government%20recently.%20The%20share%20in%20the%20total%20population%20is%201.40%25.%20This%20number%20has%20zero%20significance%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20political%20interference.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHowever%2C%20in%20Bihar%20they%20have%20been%20categorised%20as%20an%20Extremely%20Backward%20Class%2C%20while%20in%20other%20states%20of%20the%20country%20they%20are%20included%20in%20backward%20class%20lists.%20Only%20in%20Chhatarpur%2C%20Datia%2C%20Panna%2C%20Satna%2C%20Tikamgarh%2C%20Sidhi%20and%20Shahdol%20districts%20of%20Madhya%20Pradesh%20are%20they%20classified%20as%20Scheduled%20Castes.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20the%20present%20mechanical%20age%2C%20their%20traditional%20craft%20of%20moulding%20clay%20is%20dying%20out.%20But%20sometimes%20things%20change%20for%20good.%20As%20mystic%20poet%20Kabir%20once%20said%20%E2%80%93%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CGlad%20that%20my%20earthen%20pot%20broke%2C%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20am%20spared%20of%20the%20responsibility%20of%20filling%20it%20with%20water.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20truth%20is%20harsh.%20Landlessness%20and%20non-availability%20of%20employment%20have%20forced%20them%20to%20work%20as%20daily%20wage%20labourers%20or%20to%20become%20migrant%20labourers%20and%20move%20to%20other%20cities%20and%20states.%20Only%20those%20who%20know%20what%20it%20means%20to%20create%20something%20can%20understand%20their%20pain.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ETranslated%20from%20Hindi%20by%20Naushin%20Rehman.%20Read%20the%20Hindi%20original%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewirehindi.com%2F261398%2Fbihar-caste-survey-kumhar-caste-pottery-society%2F%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ERead%20earlier%20parts%20